Indian Rewards to Its Winners at Asiad
NEW DELHI , December 24 ( Xinhua ) -- Prime Minister Atal Behari Vajpayee on Thursday announced cash rewards to Indian Asian Games athletes who won medals in Bangkok , reports said .
According to Vajpayee , each gold medal winner would get 500,000 rupees ( 12,500 U.S. dollars ) , while silver and broze medallists would receive 300,000 rupees ( 7,500 U.S. dollars ) and 200,000 rupees ( 5,000 U.S. dollars ) respectively .
The awards were higher than those previously given by Indian governments to winners at international meets .
India won seven golds , 11 silver and 17 bronze medals at the Bangkok Games .
